                                <div class = "backTitle">Should school be mandatory?</div>
                                <div class = "backBody">
                                    <div class = "backSourceName">Article written by Kevin Tessier</div>
                                    <div class="backBodyText">
                                        <h2>The Premise</h2>
                                        <p>This article states that while school shouldn't be compulsory, it should still be heavily recommended and that "literacy and mathematical education to the point where you can easily handle reading, writing, and personal finances" should be mandatory.<span class = "sitedSource"><sup>[2]</sup></span>
                                        I agree with this on a basic level, but don't believe that school shouldn't be mandatory to a certain age. I think society would eventually fail if education wasn't enforced, as to few people would invest the time to get properly educated. I think an acceptable 
                                        compromise would be mandatory education to the age of 12, and then highly suggested and rewarded past that age.</p>
                                        <h2>Difficulties</h2>
                                        <p>
                                            I think the other fundamental issue with changing from mandatory to non mandatory schooling is just the logistics of converting 15,563 schools nationally to a new system. This would be a monumental task that would likely take close to a decade. To acomplish this, a prime minister would
                                            have to take up the task of converting to a new system, which would likely not be popular with the public at the time and therefore would not be something a Prime Minister would like to do.
                                        </p>

