                                <div class="backTitle">Why compulsory military service is an outdated concept from a past generation.</div>
                                <div class = "backBody">
                                    
                                    <div class = "backSourceName">Article written by Nick De Gregorio</div>
                                    <div class="backBodyText">
                                        <h2>Reasoning</h2>
                                        <p>
                                            The article cited for this argument explains why they think mandatory military service is a necessity that will unify a country. They raise several valid points, such as the all time low of citizens that have served in the military (7.3%), and the fact that the military is now seen as an expendable commodity
                                             - not as real humans with friends and families. Additionally, mandatory military service is less of a burden to the tax base during a time of war than conscription is. All of this ignores the fact, however, that when not in a time of war countries with mandatory military service (generally starting at age 21
                                             and lasting 2 years) have a smaller tax base due to the fact that the majority of the developing population is serving.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            It also quotes increased terrorist attacks in Europe as a prime reason to increase military force, to demolish terrorism once and for all. Unfortunately, this has been repeatedly proven to not be true. An increased military offence against terrorism can only assist to a point, after which it will only lead
                                                to fewer but more violent terrorist attacks.<span class = "sitedSource"><sup>[8]</sup></span>
                                        </p>
                                        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                                        <p>
                                                The benefits of mandatory military service simply do not outway the issues with it. The weakened economy, the violations of freedom, and the lack of a productive young working class simply are not worth it. I can understand the perspective that is being viewed when mandatory service is suggested, but the 
                                                fact is that it simply is not worth it.
                                        </p>
